# Health checks & hybrid DNS

## Health checks — a public-internet prober fleet

Probe from many locations, **majority decides** (~3 of 18+). Three types:

- **Endpoint** — HTTP/TCP probe on a path (2xx/3xx in 4 s); optional **string match**
- **Calculated** — AND/OR/NOT of other checks
- **CloudWatch alarm** — the **only way to check a private resource**

Feed failover / weighted / latency / multivalue → **unhealthy records dropped**.

## Hybrid DNS — Route 53 Resolver

Built-in resolver at **base+2**. Two endpoints bridge on-prem:

- **Inbound** — on-prem resolves AWS private-zone names
- **Outbound** + **Resolver Rules** — EC2 resolves on-prem names (`corp.internal` → on-prem DNS)

ENIs per AZ; rules **shareable via RAM**.
